<h3>What is this?</h3>
<p>This is a basic demo of the <a href="http://github.com/mptre/php-soundcloud/" rel="external">SoundCloud PHP API Wrapper</a> which lets you login to your SoundCloud account using <a href="http://oauth.net/2/" rel="external">OAuth 2.0</a>.</p>
<p>Once logged in the user can view his profile and upload a new track to his account. The track will be kept private by default.</p>
<p>Note that this demo neither save your login credentials or account information.</p>
<p>For further reference check out the documentation or take a look at code for this demo over at <a href="http://github.com/mptre/ci-soundcloud/" rel="external">GitHub</a>.</p>
<p>The demo and API Wrapper is developed by <a href="http://qvister.se" rel="external">Anton Lindqvist</a>.</p>
<h3>How to start?</h3>
<p>Simply by clicking the connect button below!</p>
<a id="connect" href="<?php echo $authorize_url; ?>">Connect with SoundCloud</a>